{"title":"Wand of sleep","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Wand_of_sleep","type":"markdown","data":"| /               |                                                                                 |\n| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name            | sleep                                                                           |\n| Appearance      | [random](/wiki/Randomised_appearance \"Randomised appearance\")                   |\n| Abundance       | [5%](/wiki/Wand#Generation \"Wand\")                                              |\n| Base price      | 175 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\")                                               |\n| Weight          | 7                                                                               |\n| Type            | ray                                                                             |\n| Maximum charges | 8                                                                               |\n| Spell           | [sleep](/wiki/Spellbook_of_sleep \"Spellbook of sleep\")                          |\n| Monster use     | *May be used [offensively](/wiki/Offensive_item \"Offensive item\") by monsters.* |\n\nThe **wand of sleep** is a [wand](/wiki/Wand \"Wand\") in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*.\n\n## Effect\n\nWhen zapped, it emits a [ray](/wiki/Ray \"Ray\") that puts monsters it hits to [sleep](/wiki/Sleep \"Sleep\") for 6d25 turns, unless they resist. Bolts of sleep can bounce from walls and unrevealed secret doors, but are absorbed by non-secret or discovered secret doors.\n\n## Strategy\n\nYou can use it to help defeat (or escape) a difficult [monster](/wiki/Monster \"Monster\")(s) unless they have [sleep resistance](/wiki/Sleep_resistance \"Sleep resistance\"); just be careful where the beam bounces. In a co-aligned [temple](/wiki/Temple \"Temple\"), you can use this wand to park a heavy monster on the [altar](/wiki/Altar \"Altar\") so that you can kill it there without having it run away from you.\n\nWhen engraving, this wand gives the same message as a [wand of death](/wiki/Wand_of_death \"Wand of death\"). If the wand was not generated in a monster's inventory, the odds are 6:1 for it being sleep.\n\n- *This page is a **[stub](/wiki/Category:Stubs \"Category:Stubs\")**. Should you wish to do so, you can contribute by [**expanding this page**.](https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?title=Wand_of_sleep\\&action=edit)*\n\n[![This article may require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/b/b0/Nh343-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article may require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n\n**This page may need to be updated for the [current version](/wiki/Current_version \"Current version\") of *NetHack*.**\n\nIt may contain text specific to [NetHack 3.4.3](/wiki/NetHack_3.4.3 \"NetHack 3.4.3\"). Information on this page may be out of date.\n\n**Editors:** After reviewing this page and making necessary edits, please change the {{nethack-343}} tag to the current version's tag or {{noversion}} as appropriate.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Wand of sleep - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Wand_of_sleep\",\"wgTitle\":\"Wand of sleep\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":136621,\"wgRevisionId\":136621,\"wgArticleId\":7378,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Offensive items\",\"Stubs\",\"Wands\",\"Nethack-343 articles\"],\"wgBr